<?xml version="1.0"?>
<section xml:id="ch-functions">
    <title>Review - Functions</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>Practice reading, tracing, testing, and writing simple functions.</p>
    </introduction>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part A: Recognize</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-fn-recognize">
            <statement>
                <p>Study the function below and label the function name, parameter, return statement, and function call.</p>
                <program language="python">
def double(value):
    return value * 2

result = double(5)</program>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part B: Trace</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-fn-trace">
            <statement>
                <program language="python">
def add_one(num):
    return num + 1</program>
                <p>What value is returned by <c>add_one(4)</c>,                    <c>add_one(10)</c>, and <c>add_one(-1)</c>?
                </p>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part C: Match</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-fn-match">
            <statement>
                <p>Match each function to its purpose.</p>
                <program language="python">
def square(x):
    return x * x

def greet(name):
    return "Hello, " + name

def is_positive(num):
    return num > 0</program>
                <p>Purposes: returns a greeting string; checks whether a number is positive; returns the square of a number.</p>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part D: Fix</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-fn-fix">
            <statement>
                <p>Correct the errors in the function below.</p>
                <program language="python">
def multiply(a, b)
    result = a * b
    print return result</program>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Part E: Create</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-fn-create">
            <statement>
                <p>Write a function named <c>subtract</c> that takes two parameters and returns the difference of the first minus the second. Then write three test calls.</p>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
    <subsection>
        <title>Think About ...</title>
        <exercise xml:id="ex-fn-reflection">
            <statement>
                <p>What is the difference between <c>print()</c> and <c>return</c> inside a function?</p>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
    </subsection>
</section>